%H A036058 <a href="/index/Con#constant">Index of eventually constant sequences</a>.
%F A036058 a(n+1) = A244112(a(n)), a(0) = 0. - _M. F. Hasler_, Feb 25 2018
%e A036058 The third term is 1110 because the second term contains one 1 and one 0.
%t A036058 PadRight[#, 30, #[[-1]]] &@ FixedPointList[FromDigits@ Flatten@ ReverseSortBy[Map[Reverse, Tally@ IntegerDigits[#] ], Last] &, 0] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Sep 14 2025 *)
